<paragraph id="8BFF3685B645FF910A27FD3BBA715BE7" blockId="7.[264,1324,283,1033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
The specific name, 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910933FD3BBCED5BBC" box="[556,687,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritae">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910933FD3BBCED5BBC" box="[556,687,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">margaritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is a Latinized feminine noun in the genitive case. 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910A17FD13BC4E5BE4" box="[264,524,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritae">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910A17FD13BC4E5BE4" box="[264,524,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Empoasca margaritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named for my daughter, Margaret Southern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF3685B645FF910A27FD6BBA185D28" blockId="7.[264,1324,283,1033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
In the key to 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910AC8FD6BBC135BCC" box="[471,593,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910AC8FD6BBC135BCC" box="[471,593,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Empoasca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3577615B645FF9109C9FD6BBD4E5BCF" box="[726,780,724,750]" name="Peru" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B74B645FF910802FD6BBD955BCF" author="Southern" box="[797,983,724,750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="51" refString="Southern, P. S. (1982) A taxonomic study of the leafhopper genus Empoasca (Homoptera: Cicadellidae in eastern Peru. Technical Bulletin 272. North Carolina State University, Raleigh, N. C., 194 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Southern, 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910887FD6BBD955BCF" box="[920,983,724,750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF9108F2FD6BBAD35BCC" box="[1005,1169,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritae">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF9108F2FD6BBAD35BCC" box="[1005,1169,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">E. margaritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys well to couplet 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910A78FD43BFC55A37" box="[359,391,764,790]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="27.0">27</number>
, and, assuming the anal hook is considered broadly rounded, goes reasonably well to couplet 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910ADBFC9BBFA75A1F" box="[452,485,804,830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="28.0">28</number>
. Couplet 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910947FC9BBC375A1F" box="[600,629,804,830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="28.0">28</number>
separates 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF9109EBFC9BBDB55A1F" authority="Southern" authorityName="Southern" box="[756,1015,804,830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculata">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF9109EBFC9BBDC65A1C" box="[756,900,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">E. aciculata</emphasis>
Southern
</taxonomicName>
from certain members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910A2CFCF3BFE05A44" box="[307,418,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solana">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910A2CFCF3BFE05A44" box="[307,418,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">E. solana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (now usually treated as 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910833FCF3BA015A47" authority="Ghauri 1974" authorityName="Ghauri" authorityYear="1974" box="[812,1091,844,870]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Solanasca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910833FCF3BDE75A44" box="[812,933,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Solanasca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B74B645FF9108B4FCF3BA015A47" author="Ghauri" box="[939,1091,844,870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="51" refString="Ghauri, M. S. K. (1974) The solana - group of Empoasca Walsh (Homoptera, Cicadelloidea): its generic status and a new species from pawpaw. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 63, 425 - 429." type="journal article" year="1974">
Ghauri 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910F1BFCF3BA015A47" box="[1028,1091,844,870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). In couplet 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910FCBFCF3BAB65A47" box="[1236,1268,844,870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="28.0">28</number>
, this species keys most closely to 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF91097AFCCBBCB75AAC" box="[613,757,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculata">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF91097AFCCBBCB75AAC" box="[613,757,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">E. aciculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910819FCCBBDEE5AAC" box="[774,940,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritae">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910819FCCBBDEE5AAC" box="[774,940,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">E. margaritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D06B645FF910F52FCCBBA9F5AAC" box="[1101,1245,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculata">
<emphasis id="B934EA97B645FF910F52FCCBBA9F5AAC" box="[1101,1245,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">E. aciculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the form of the pygofer process, which is not tapered evenly to an acute apex; in the form of the style, which is clubbed apically; in the shape of the aedeagus; and in the size of the second sternal apodemes, which barely reach the 
<number id="3D8824A2B645FF910853FC50BD185D28" box="[844,858,1007,1033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
th abdominal segment.
</paragraph>
